---
title: "FAQ — Slade Networks"
description: "Answers to common questions about pricing, payment, timelines, and what to expect from a Slade Networks installation in the Finger Lakes, NY."
navActive: faq
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .section { padding: 12px 0 60px }
    .ctaSection { padding: 0 0 72px }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
          Common questions answered
        </div>
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          Practical answers about cost, timelines, and how projects work — before you reach out.
        </p>

        <div class="callout">
          <div>
            <h2>Don't see your question?</h2>
            <p>Reach out directly — we're happy to help.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Get in touch</a>
            <a class="btn" href="mailto:info@sladenetworks.com?subject=Slade%20Networks%20Question">Email us</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">Before you start</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                How much does it cost?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Pricing depends on the scope — the size of the space, what's being installed, how much cabling is involved, and what equipment is needed. No two projects are the same, so there's no flat rate.
                <br><br>
                Equipment and labor are always quoted together. You'll receive a written, itemized quote before any work begins — no surprises when the invoice arrives.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How does payment work?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Equipment is billed before the install — this covers the cost of hardware ordered specifically for your project. Labor is billed once the installation is complete and you're satisfied with the work.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How far out are you booking?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Typically 1–2 weeks out. Reach out and we'll find a time that works.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do you serve my area?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                We're based in Penn Yan and serve the Finger Lakes region — including Keuka Park, Hammondsport, Watkins Glen, Geneva, Canandaigua, Naples, Victor, and Auburn. If you're a bit outside that range, reach out anyway — travel is possible depending on the project.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do you work with homes, businesses, or both?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Both. Residential projects are typically Wi-Fi upgrades, camera installs, and home office setups. Business projects tend to involve more cabling, switching, phone systems, and ongoing support. The process is the same either way — free on-site visit, written quote, clean install.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">The project</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                Can you fix an existing setup, or only do new installs?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Both. Many projects are upgrades or fixes — poor Wi-Fi in certain rooms, cameras that aren't recording reliably, a disorganized rack. We'll look at what you have, figure out what's causing the issue, and give you a clear plan to resolve it.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How long does a project take?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Smaller jobs — a Wi-Fi upgrade, a camera add-on — are usually done in a few hours or a single visit. A full install with cabling, cameras, Wi-Fi, and a new rack typically takes 1–2 days. You'll get a realistic timeline in your written quote before any work begins.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do I need to buy equipment first?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                No. Equipment sourcing is handled as part of the project and included in your quote. If you already have gear you'd like to keep, we'll evaluate it and use what makes sense — just mention it when you reach out.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                My internet is slow — is that something you can fix?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                It depends on where the problem is. Slow speeds inside your home or office — while the connection at the modem is fine — are a network problem we can fix. If your ISP is delivering less than you're paying for, that's on them and outside what we do.
                <br><br>
                Not sure which it is? We can help figure that out during the consultation.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do you run cable through walls?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Yes. In-wall runs are part of most installs — that's how you get clean results without cables running along baseboards. We plan routes carefully to minimize any drywall work, and where cuts are unavoidable, they're kept small and tidy.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">After the install</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do I keep full access to my own system?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Yes. You get admin credentials and a complete walkthrough at handoff. Your system is yours — nothing is locked behind our login.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Is the work guaranteed?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Yes. If something isn't right due to the installation itself, it gets fixed at no charge. Hardware is covered by the manufacturer's warranty — typically 1–2 years for UniFi equipment. If a device fails outside of installation error, we can diagnose it remotely and advise on next steps.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Who can access my camera footage?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Only you. Footage is recorded locally to a network video recorder (NVR) on your own premises — it's not stored in the cloud or accessible to anyone without your credentials. Remote access is set up for you and only shared with whoever you choose.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How do I get help after the install?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Email <a href="mailto:support@sladenetworks.com">support@sladenetworks.com</a>. If remote access is configured on your system, most issues can be diagnosed and resolved without scheduling a site visit.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Still have questions?</h2>
            <p>The fastest way to get answers is to schedule a free consultation. We'll cover everything specific to your space and situation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Book a consultation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
